  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 6</p>\n<p>Peel and cut the <strong>sweet potato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> into chips</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>sweet potato chips</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\n<p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp  </p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/new-york-style-ham-and-cheese-melt/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Slice 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8]</span> discs from the <strong>cucumber </strong>(these will go in your sandwich later!)</p>\n<p>Slice the <strong>remaining cucumber</strong> in half lengthways, then slice the halves into wedges</p>\n<p>Chop the <strong>dill</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/new-york-style-ham-and-cheese-melt/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>chopped dill</strong>, <strong>black</strong> <strong>mustard seeds</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>, a splash of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a bowl and stir until dissolved</p>\n<p>Add <strong>all</strong> of the <strong>sliced cucumber</strong> to the vinegar, give everything a good mix up and set aside – this is your <strong>pickled cucumber</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/new-york-style-ham-and-cheese-melt/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>cheddar cheese</strong> in quarters lengthways</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/new-york-style-ham-and-cheese-melt/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the<strong> ciabatta rolls </strong>in half</p>\n<p>Spread the <strong>ciabatta base</strong> with the <strong>mustard ketchup</strong></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>shredded</strong> <strong>ham hock</strong> to the <strong>ciabatta base</strong>, and top with the <strong>cheddar cheese </strong>and add to a baking tray with the <strong>ciabatta lids</strong> (cut side up)</p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 3-4 mins or until the cheese has melted</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/new-york-style-ham-and-cheese-melt/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the cheese has melted, remove the tray from the oven and spread<strong> mayonnaise</strong> over the <strong>ciabatta lids</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/new-york-style-ham-and-cheese-melt/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Layer the <strong>pickled cucumber discs</strong> on top of the <strong>melted cheese</strong> and top with the <strong>ciabatta lid </strong>– this is your<strong> New York melt</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/new-york-style-ham-and-cheese-melt/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>New York melt</strong> with the <strong>sweet potato chips</strong> and remaining <strong>pickled cucumber</strong> <strong>wedges</strong> to the side</p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
